ce:section.ce:para:
Photoelectrochemical measurements were performed on an electrochemical workstation (CHI 760E, shanghai, China) with the three-electrode system, where the as-prepared electrodes were regarded as working electrodes. The visible light was provided by a 300 W Xenon lamp (Beijing ceaulight, λ ≥ 420 nm) with a light intensity of 100 mW/cm2. Aeration was not provided. The distance between the two electrodes was 2 cm, and the entire reaction process was kept stirring without an external resistor. I-t curves and linear sweep voltammetry (LSV) were tested in 0.1 M Na2SO3-Na2SO4 mixture with the light on/off. Mott-Schottky curves (M−S) and Electrochemical impedance spectroscopy (EIS) were obtained in 0.5 M Na2SO4. The short-circuit current density (Jsc
                        ) and open-circuit voltage (Voc
                        ) of the PFC system were tested in 0.1 M Na2SO4.
